Invention:  Vaccine
Year:       1796
Inventor:   Edward Jenner
Country:    England
Category:   Medicine
Description:Cowpox inoculation against smallpox
Impact:     Saved billions; smallpox eradicated; immunology foundation

Invention:  Penicillin
Year:       1928
Inventor:   Alexander Fleming
Country:    Scotland
Category:   Medicine
Description:First antibiotic from mold
Impact:     Saved estimated 200 million lives

Invention:  Computer
Year:       1945
Inventor:   Mauchly/Eckert
Country:    USA
Category:   Computing
Description:ENIAC: first electronic computer
Impact:     Digital revolution; led to all modern computing

